Generated the Focus Manager developer guide at `docs/generated/focus-manager.md`. The document covers:

- Getting the FocusManager singleton
- Setting focus with `RequestFocus()` and `SetCurrentFocusView()`
- Moving focus directionally with `MoveFocus()` and `FocusDirection` enum values
- Focus groups for trapping focus within view subtrees
- Custom focus indicators
- Focus change signals for reacting to focus events
- Window focus behavior configuration
- Focus device information for determining input source

All API examples are grounded in the public headers (`focus-manager.h`, `view-focus-enums.h`) and verified against the UTC test cases.
